text.section:
For the purposes of this section, average density shall be calculated based on the total acreage of all parcels in the area for which the principal permitted use is residential, excluding land:
dedicated for public use by easement in perpetuity or fee acquisition; or
dedicated recreational use;
subject to an agricultural easement under § 2-508 of the Agriculture Article;
subject to an agricultural easement under a county agricultural land preservation program certified under § 5-408 of this title;
used for cemetery purposes;
identified by a local government as:
streams and their buffers;
100-year flood plains;
habitats of threatened and endangered species; and
steep slopes; and
on which development is prohibited by local law or ordinance; or
identified by a local government as delineated nontidal wetlands on which development is prohibited by State or local law or ordinance.
